notesStmt.note: Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 18; written lines: 13 18; Uniform layout. Larger square initial words, partly in red ink. Hard-point ruling (complete) visible. Last written line outside ruling. Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable. Most of the catchwords cut off in trimming. Partly vocalised.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Italian square and semi-cursive, and Ashkenazi square script of the 15th century.

binding.p: Post 1600. Brown leather, blind tooled, with remains of clasps. Boxed. Spine: 'Prayer Book. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental Ms. 13260.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Acquired by the British Museum in 1970.
